subjective, "joining hands" relationships that 15M has brought into being and works to carry on in creative ways. The book shows how the movement’s way of being and temporality persists in Spain following the square occupations, while 15M citizens continue to learn and move forward in less perceptible ways. Democracy Here and Now sheds light on a deeply relational, intersectional, and eco-social mode of democracy, and shows how 15M’s ongoing democratization practices are exemplary of similar grassroots movements around the world, broadening our understandings of what it means to be democratic in the here and now.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aDemocratizationzSpainxHistoryy21st century. 0aPolitical participationzSpainxHistoryy21st century. 0aProtest movementszSpainxHistoryy21st century. 0aSocial movementszSpainxHistoryy21st century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  a15M.  aCatalan politics.  aSpain.  ademocratization practices.  ajoining hands relationships.  anonviolent contestation.  aparticipatory and representative democracy.  apopulism.  asocial change.1 aTully, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTully, James.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148754319840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487543198423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487543198/original  a978-3-11-076715-5  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK